WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:center
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:00.270 --> 00:00:03.140
Open up the borderless map, then

3
00:00:03.140 --> 00:00:06.340
Head for that unknown edge of the ocean

4
00:00:06.340 --> 00:00:10.730
LET’S SAIL ON right now, hoist your sails up high

5
00:00:10.730 --> 00:00:13.720
Riding on the wind

6
00:00:18.850 --> 00:00:23.060
DON’T GIVE UP, it’s time to finish what we started

7
00:00:23.250 --> 00:00:26.030
So don't you grow disheartened

8
00:00:26.340 --> 00:00:29.790
Laugh the tears away through the storm

9
00:00:29.990 --> 00:00:34.220
SHOUT IT OUT, when you feel down always remember

10
00:00:34.560 --> 00:00:36.820
That’s what your friends are there for

11
00:00:36.850 --> 00:00:38.980
Y’know there’s no point in fronting,

12
00:00:38.980 --> 00:00:42.900
your crew will always have your back

13
00:00:43.270 --> 00:00:47.000
Even in the face of utter darkness

14
00:00:47.230 --> 00:00:49.990
C’mon, BRAVE IT OUT We’ll be alright

15
00:00:50.290 --> 00:00:53.780
Together you know that we’ll never lose a fight

16
00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:56.770
Open up the borderless map, then

17
00:00:56.790 --> 00:00:59.630
Head for that unknown edge of the ocean

18
00:00:59.930 --> 00:01:04.210
All great journeys starts with a single step

19
00:01:04.280 --> 00:01:05.220
DREAMIN’ ON

20
00:01:05.220 --> 00:01:08.000
Open up the borderless map, then

21
00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:10.740
Raise the flag we swore to defend

22
00:01:10.890 --> 00:01:13.630
We’ll never stop until we’ve reached the top

23
00:01:13.700 --> 00:01:18.100
Just be true to yourself until the end

24
00:01:18.230 --> 00:01:22.940
Set sail and grab it, DREAMIN ON

25
00:01:31.860 --> 00:01:36.700
Twenty-eight years ago
on the second year of Oden's voyage...

26
00:01:31.900 --> 00:01:36.830
<b>28 Years Ago

Second Year
of Oden's Voyage</b>

27
00:01:36.950 --> 00:01:41.500
<b>Roger and Whitebeard</b>

28
00:01:39.370 --> 00:01:41.500
The baby is finally here!

29
00:01:41.500 --> 00:01:42.500
Tamago!

30
00:01:42.500 --> 00:01:43.500
Konbu!

31
00:01:43.500 --> 00:01:44.500
Chikuwa!

32
00:01:44.500 --> 00:01:45.420
Tsukune!

33
00:01:46.130 --> 00:01:49.340
Hey, knock it off! He's a baby,
not a pot of oden!

34
00:01:50.090 --> 00:01:51.880
This is our first child!

35
00:01:52.550 --> 00:01:54.590
The name I give you means peerless...

36
00:01:56.300 --> 00:01:59.970
You shall be called Kozuki Momonosuke!

37
00:02:03.020 --> 00:02:05.730
Lord Oden, they have issued
wanted posters for you.

38
00:02:06.150 --> 00:02:09.530
I am afraid you are now
a fully-fledged outlaw overseas.

39
00:02:09.530 --> 00:02:12.150
For Lady Toki and Lord Momonosuke's safety,

40
00:02:12.150 --> 00:02:15.910
perhaps you should consider
returning to Wano.

41
00:02:15.910 --> 00:02:19.410
Not yet, Izo! I have yet to find my answer!

42
00:02:19.410 --> 00:02:22.750
We will be fine. Do not worry!

43
00:02:22.750 --> 00:02:25.330
This thing may be called a newspaper,

44
00:02:25.330 --> 00:02:29.000
but there's no news about Wano in it!

45
00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:33.510
Well, just like Zou, they have no method
of sending info outside the country.

46
00:02:34.050 --> 00:02:36.550
I wonder meow Kin
and the others are doing?

47
00:02:42.060 --> 00:02:43.600
What?!

48
00:02:43.600 --> 00:02:45.310
You are appointing commanders?!

49
00:02:45.310 --> 00:02:47.360
Our crew keeps on growing.

50
00:02:47.360 --> 00:02:51.820
How do you feel about
splitting into five or so divisions?

51
00:02:51.820 --> 00:02:54.570
That's a great idea, Pops!

52
00:02:54.570 --> 00:02:56.660
I wanna be a commander!

53
00:02:56.660 --> 00:02:58.200
Me, too!

54
00:02:58.200 --> 00:02:59.660
Oden!

55
00:03:00.080 --> 00:03:02.450
You will lead the second division!

56
00:03:03.080 --> 00:03:07.250
Well... Um... Uh... Um...

57
00:03:09.090 --> 00:03:09.960
Just do it!

58
00:03:11.590 --> 00:03:15.840
Newcomers would join the crew
from time to time, much like we had...

59
00:03:15.840 --> 00:03:17.050
Listen!

60
00:03:17.050 --> 00:03:19.720
This ain't no fishing boat! We're pirates!

61
00:03:19.720 --> 00:03:21.560
P-Please!

62
00:03:22.140 --> 00:03:24.310
I've got nowhere else to go!

63
00:03:24.310 --> 00:03:26.270
Hey, knock it off!

64
00:03:26.270 --> 00:03:27.480
What's your name?

65
00:03:29.520 --> 00:03:31.110
Teach!

66
00:03:35.400 --> 00:03:36.950
Very well.

67
00:03:36.950 --> 00:03:38.110
Come aboard!

68
00:03:40.700 --> 00:03:42.700
Thank you so much!

69
00:03:44.410 --> 00:03:47.330
Another orphan it would seem...

70
00:03:49.630 --> 00:03:50.630
Did you see that?

71
00:03:50.630 --> 00:03:52.590
Something just flew past us!

72
00:03:54.090 --> 00:03:57.630
No matter how far I sail,
my curiosity is never satiated!

73
00:03:57.630 --> 00:03:59.510
Commander!

74
00:03:59.510 --> 00:04:01.890
We need to scout the area first!

75
00:04:02.260 --> 00:04:06.270
I do not know how to end such an adventure!

76
00:04:07.600 --> 00:04:10.810
Meanwhile, in Wano...

77
00:04:10.810 --> 00:04:12.480
Extra, extra!

78
00:04:12.480 --> 00:04:14.150
Read all about it!

79
00:04:14.150 --> 00:04:18.910
The shogun, Lord Sukiyaki,
is in critical condition!

80
00:04:18.910 --> 00:04:20.410
Lord Sukiyaki!

81
00:04:20.410 --> 00:04:22.620
Within Wano's borders...

82
00:04:23.410 --> 00:04:29.370
a grave matter brought the daimyo
of each region to the Flower Capital.

83
00:04:32.130 --> 00:04:34.630
I wish for Oden...

84
00:04:35.250 --> 00:04:37.510
to succeed me as shogun.

85
00:04:37.510 --> 00:04:40.430
Of course, Lord Sukiyaki!

86
00:04:42.220 --> 00:04:46.100
But seeing as Oden is abroad at the moment,

87
00:04:46.100 --> 00:04:51.400
it appears I must appoint
a proxy in his absence...

88
00:04:52.150 --> 00:04:54.820
in the event anything should befall me.

89
00:04:56.320 --> 00:05:01.110
I have chosen the man Oden cared for
as though he were his younger brother...

90
00:05:01.110 --> 00:05:03.160
Kurozumi Orochi!

91
00:05:06.120 --> 00:05:07.910
Orochi?

92
00:05:08.540 --> 00:05:09.870
What are you doing here?

93
00:05:11.960 --> 00:05:15.210
Oden cared for him as though
he were his younger brother?

94
00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:16.880
Is that true?

95
00:05:18.300 --> 00:05:23.050
Thank you for allowing me to atone for
the sins of the Kurozumi Clan.

96
00:05:23.050 --> 00:05:28.600
I am unworthy to even look Lord Sukiyaki
and Lord Oden in the eye!

97
00:05:29.060 --> 00:05:32.770
To compensate for
the follies of my grandfather,

98
00:05:32.770 --> 00:05:38.530
I will assist Lord Oden's enthronement
to the best of my ability!

99
00:05:41.240 --> 00:05:46.830
I shall be your willing puppet
until Lord Oden returns,

100
00:05:46.830 --> 00:05:50.160
so I must ask for everyone's support!

101
00:05:50.790 --> 00:05:52.460
So you're a Kurozumi...

102
00:05:52.460 --> 00:05:54.210
Why didn't you tell me?

103
00:05:54.210 --> 00:05:56.090
Oh, my apologies!

104
00:06:00.800 --> 00:06:03.050
My apologies...!

105
00:06:15.350 --> 00:06:16.650
I can see it!

106
00:06:16.650 --> 00:06:18.270
I can see the future!

107
00:06:19.190 --> 00:06:21.070
You'll...

108
00:06:26.070 --> 00:06:28.450
become shogun!

109
00:06:34.250 --> 00:06:35.960
You scared me, old hag!

110
00:06:35.960 --> 00:06:37.500
Who the hell are you?!

111
00:06:41.170 --> 00:06:44.840
Are you unaware of what happened
to your grandfather?

112
00:06:45.640 --> 00:06:49.850
I don't know all the details,
but I heard he committed seppuku.

113
00:06:49.850 --> 00:06:53.560
Wrong! It was the Kozuki Clan that killed him!

114
00:06:53.560 --> 00:06:54.310
What?!

115
00:06:54.310 --> 00:06:56.770
But I heard he committed some kind of crime!

116
00:06:56.770 --> 00:06:59.820
Engaging in a power struggle isn't a crime!

117
00:07:00.320 --> 00:07:02.440
It was... a power struggle?

118
00:07:02.440 --> 00:07:05.490
If you take the reins, you can make the laws!

119
00:07:06.200 --> 00:07:08.820
You decide what's a crime and what isn't!

120
00:07:08.820 --> 00:07:15.750
The previous shogun from the Kozuki Clan...
was unable to sire any children!

121
00:07:15.750 --> 00:07:17.580
He had no heirs!

122
00:07:18.170 --> 00:07:22.840
Naturally, the five clans serving under
the Kozuki Clan began to wonder...

123
00:07:22.920 --> 00:07:29.180
<b>Shimotsuki
Clan</b>

124
00:07:23.340 --> 00:07:25.550
who was going to be the next shogun?

125
00:07:24.170 --> 00:07:29.180
<b>Kurozumi
Clan</b>

126
00:07:25.170 --> 00:07:29.180
<b>Uzuki
Clan</b>

127
00:07:25.550 --> 00:07:29.180
While the others pompously assumed
they would be selected,

128
00:07:26.170 --> 00:07:29.180
<b>Amatsuki
Clan</b>

129
00:07:27.170 --> 00:07:29.180
<b>Fugetsu
Clan</b>

130
00:07:29.890 --> 00:07:34.100
your grandfather had already
begun making preparations!

131
00:07:34.100 --> 00:07:39.480
He devised a plan to poison
those irksome daimyo one by one!

132
00:07:40.560 --> 00:07:45.150
He got rid of them one after another,
making them all look like inside jobs!

133
00:07:45.150 --> 00:07:49.160
The series of daimyo deaths was
too much for the shogun,

134
00:07:49.160 --> 00:07:51.910
and he eventually took ill.

135
00:07:52.240 --> 00:07:54.660
His plan had been flawless!

136
00:07:54.660 --> 00:08:00.250
But just as he was within
reach of seizing power...

137
00:08:02.590 --> 00:08:04.960
that brat was born...!

138
00:08:05.380 --> 00:08:08.680
The heir, Kozuki Sukiyaki!

139
00:08:09.930 --> 00:08:11.220
– Yes!
– Yes!

140
00:08:11.220 --> 00:08:13.310
Congratulations!

141
00:08:14.560 --> 00:08:18.390
A curse on you, Sukiyaki!

142
00:08:19.480 --> 00:08:22.060
He was only one step away from power,

143
00:08:22.060 --> 00:08:26.240
and to make matters worse,
his plan was exposed!

144
00:08:26.240 --> 00:08:30.490
Your grandfather committed seppuku,
and the clan was removed from power!

145
00:08:31.280 --> 00:08:34.490
Their territory, castle,
and power were all taken away.

146
00:08:34.490 --> 00:08:37.000
People grew to despise the Kurozumi name,

147
00:08:37.000 --> 00:08:41.250
and the members of the clan
ended up on the streets!

148
00:08:41.250 --> 00:08:43.960
Whose fault could that be?!

149
00:08:45.340 --> 00:08:48.880
Who was it that made your life so miserable?!

150
00:08:48.880 --> 00:08:52.050
Who's responsible for your poverty?!

151
00:08:52.760 --> 00:08:54.930
Upon whom does the blame fall?!

152
00:08:56.890 --> 00:08:58.350
It's because he was birthed!

153
00:09:00.390 --> 00:09:02.100
Kozuki Sukiyaki!

154
00:09:02.480 --> 00:09:04.270
That's right!

155
00:09:04.270 --> 00:09:09.070
If he had never been born,
you would have one day become shogun!

156
00:09:10.490 --> 00:09:12.660
My lord, Shogun!

157
00:09:12.660 --> 00:09:14.080
I love you!

158
00:09:14.080 --> 00:09:16.040
My lord, Shogun!

159
00:09:16.040 --> 00:09:17.500
I love you!

160
00:09:17.500 --> 00:09:20.920
My lord, Shogun!

161
00:09:22.170 --> 00:09:23.210
What beauties!

162
00:09:25.130 --> 00:09:26.090
I'd have...

163
00:09:26.500 --> 00:09:27.670
become shogun?!

164
00:09:27.670 --> 00:09:29.470
That's right!

165
00:09:29.470 --> 00:09:32.550
Oh, how aggravating! How galling!

166
00:09:33.340 --> 00:09:35.930
Don't tell me you're my...

167
00:09:36.470 --> 00:09:39.850
That is to say, a fellow Kurozumi?

168
00:09:39.850 --> 00:09:43.020
It doesn't matter who I am!

169
00:09:43.600 --> 00:09:46.190
I was out of the country all this time.

170
00:09:46.190 --> 00:09:48.400
It was quite the ordeal...

171
00:09:48.400 --> 00:09:51.320
But watch my face.

172
00:09:52.490 --> 00:09:53.240
What?!

173
00:09:54.780 --> 00:09:56.080
What?!

174
00:09:56.080 --> 00:09:57.740
Is that my face?!

175
00:10:01.160 --> 00:10:04.500
It's the power of the Clone-Clone Fruit.

176
00:10:06.210 --> 00:10:11.550
Should you follow my instructions,
I'm willing to bestow upon you a power of your own.

177
00:10:12.010 --> 00:10:14.720
You'll need this power
if you're to become shogun!

178
00:10:15.760 --> 00:10:18.100
I'll...! I'll do anything!

179
00:10:20.520 --> 00:10:23.940
Then begin hoarding money
and manufacturing weapons.

180
00:10:23.940 --> 00:10:27.270
Wano's craftsmen are incredibly skilled!

181
00:10:27.270 --> 00:10:31.740
With them as bait, I'm sure
you can lure in some big-time backers!

182
00:10:33.150 --> 00:10:34.200
I understand!

183
00:10:48.090 --> 00:10:51.510
<b>Hakumai</b>

184
00:10:49.750 --> 00:10:51.510
My name is Orochi.

185
00:10:51.510 --> 00:10:54.340
My whole family has fallen ill,

186
00:10:54.340 --> 00:10:59.390
so I must find a way to feed all of them...

187
00:11:00.260 --> 00:11:02.270
That is most unfortunate.

188
00:11:02.270 --> 00:11:03.640
Work for me.

189
00:11:05.560 --> 00:11:07.940
<b>A Month

Later</b>

190
00:11:06.400 --> 00:11:07.940
Lord Yasuie!

191
00:11:07.940 --> 00:11:10.730
What? Orochi has disappeared?

192
00:11:10.730 --> 00:11:11.440
Yes, sir.

193
00:11:12.110 --> 00:11:15.740
And while it is likely just a coincidence,

194
00:11:15.740 --> 00:11:18.070
the money in the safe is gone, too.

195
00:11:18.070 --> 00:11:19.450
What?

196
00:11:20.120 --> 00:11:22.120
The money is gone, too?

197
00:11:23.250 --> 00:11:26.210
<b>Kuri</b>

198
00:11:26.210 --> 00:11:29.170
You are that fellow from Yasu's place...

199
00:11:29.170 --> 00:11:30.750
My name is Orochi!

200
00:11:31.170 --> 00:11:34.170
I owe Lord Yasuie so much,

201
00:11:34.170 --> 00:11:36.260
so I can't borrow money from him!

202
00:11:37.180 --> 00:11:39.390
I understand. You can count on me!

203
00:11:39.390 --> 00:11:40.600
Lord Oden?!

204
00:11:39.390 --> 00:11:41.680
You have my gratitude!

205
00:11:44.850 --> 00:11:46.390
Lend me money!

206
00:11:46.390 --> 00:11:47.690
Again?!

207
00:11:48.480 --> 00:11:50.020
Lend me money!

208
00:11:50.020 --> 00:11:51.400
Again?!

209
00:11:54.110 --> 00:11:56.240
Please lend me money!

210
00:11:56.240 --> 00:11:59.320
I can pay you back for sure this time!

211
00:11:59.320 --> 00:12:01.120
I'm begging you!

212
00:12:03.290 --> 00:12:05.000
Lord Oden...!

213
00:12:05.000 --> 00:12:09.750
We are not doing well financially, either!

214
00:12:09.750 --> 00:12:12.290
He says he will pay it back!

215
00:12:12.290 --> 00:12:14.260
<b>Flower

Capital</b>

216
00:12:14.260 --> 00:12:18.970
<b>Kozuki Sukiyaki

(Oden's Father)

Shogun of Wano</b>

217
00:12:14.630 --> 00:12:17.470
Oden, why the sudden visit?

218
00:12:17.470 --> 00:12:18.970
And without your retainers.

219
00:12:18.970 --> 00:12:21.600
Could you let this man stay here?

220
00:12:21.600 --> 00:12:24.600
He is a hard worker
and can even prepare medicine.

221
00:12:24.600 --> 00:12:26.850
He is like a younger brother to me.

222
00:12:27.310 --> 00:12:29.190
My name is Orochi.

223
00:12:32.060 --> 00:12:35.360
Everyone, please look after Orochi!

224
00:12:35.860 --> 00:12:37.650
Very well, my lord!

225
00:12:47.540 --> 00:12:50.040
Shogun Sukiyaki!

226
00:12:50.500 --> 00:12:53.210
I've finally made it this far!

227
00:12:54.300 --> 00:13:00.260
<b>Back to

Where We

Started</b>

228
00:13:05.890 --> 00:13:08.770
Lord Sukiyaki! Stay with us!

229
00:13:08.770 --> 00:13:11.520
Lord Sukiyaki!

230
00:13:12.770 --> 00:13:15.480
Should anything befall me...

231
00:13:15.900 --> 00:13:17.610
I'm counting on you, Orochi!

232
00:13:20.280 --> 00:13:22.990
Of course, my lord!

233
00:13:23.410 --> 00:13:25.660
You, too, men.

234
00:13:25.660 --> 00:13:28.290
Lend Orochi your support.

235
00:13:28.290 --> 00:13:29.410
– My lord.
– My lord.

236
00:13:29.410 --> 00:13:30.410
Lord Sukiyaki!

237
00:13:30.410 --> 00:13:31.920
I-I'll go fetch a doctor!

238
00:13:31.920 --> 00:13:33.880
We'll be right back!

239
00:13:33.880 --> 00:13:35.590
Help! Is somebody there?!

240
00:13:35.590 --> 00:13:36.800
We need a doctor!

241
00:13:36.800 --> 00:13:38.170
Lord Sukiyaki!

242
00:13:38.170 --> 00:13:40.800
Are you all right, Lord Sukiyaki?!

243
00:13:40.800 --> 00:13:43.140
Take care of everything, Orochi!

244
00:13:43.140 --> 00:13:46.430
Stay strong, Lord Sukiyaki!

245
00:13:55.400 --> 00:13:57.650
You're gonna become shogun!

246
00:14:02.700 --> 00:14:04.780
Not long afterward,

247
00:14:04.780 --> 00:14:09.660
the news of Shogun Sukiyaki's
death spread throughout Wano.

248
00:14:21.550 --> 00:14:25.050
One day, in the fourth year
of Oden's voyage...

249
00:14:25.930 --> 00:14:27.510
What?!

250
00:14:28.640 --> 00:14:30.310
What's going on?!

251
00:14:31.100 --> 00:14:33.600
The fish are going crazy!

252
00:14:34.230 --> 00:14:36.480
Is some kinda natural disaster coming?!

253
00:14:40.570 --> 00:14:43.400
They are swimming away
from that island, Whitekichi!

254
00:14:44.070 --> 00:14:45.200
Yeah...

255
00:14:45.610 --> 00:14:48.370
Maybe some kind of monster lives there.

256
00:14:48.370 --> 00:14:50.490
Marco, go take a look!

257
00:14:50.490 --> 00:14:52.830
No way! I don't wanna spoil the fun!

258
00:15:00.460 --> 00:15:02.090
Do not fret, Hiyori!

259
00:15:02.090 --> 00:15:04.050
It is nothing, Momonosuke!

260
00:15:05.680 --> 00:15:07.760
Should we check it out, Pops?

261
00:15:09.010 --> 00:15:10.260
Why not?

262
00:15:15.390 --> 00:15:16.600
Let's go ashore!

263
00:15:16.600 --> 00:15:18.940
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

264
00:15:33.540 --> 00:15:35.790
What? This is unreal!

265
00:15:35.790 --> 00:15:38.830
Are those savage animals running away?

266
00:15:39.500 --> 00:15:41.800
The must be something on the island...

267
00:15:47.630 --> 00:15:50.140
If you really wanna catch me,

268
00:15:50.140 --> 00:15:52.930
at least bring Garp or Sengoku.

269
00:15:54.020 --> 00:15:56.810
It's no fun fighting you lackeys!

270
00:15:58.480 --> 00:15:59.770
Captain!

271
00:16:00.270 --> 00:16:03.190
Whitebeard's ship just docked
on the opposite beach!

272
00:16:03.190 --> 00:16:05.740
Seems they've noticed us!

273
00:16:05.740 --> 00:16:08.990
We just wrapped up a fight, Roger.

274
00:16:09.910 --> 00:16:11.450
Whitebeard, huh?

275
00:16:11.450 --> 00:16:12.990
It's been a while.

276
00:16:17.580 --> 00:16:19.420
The birds seem distressed...

277
00:16:19.420 --> 00:16:20.750
They must've come ashore.

278
00:16:21.170 --> 00:16:22.630
Alright!

279
00:16:22.630 --> 00:16:24.800
Let's have at it!

280
00:16:24.800 --> 00:16:27.300
You can't fight once you're dead.

281
00:16:29.050 --> 00:16:31.760
And my time is almost up.

282
00:16:31.760 --> 00:16:36.930
This could be the last time
we ever meet, Whitebeard.

283
00:16:36.930 --> 00:16:38.230
Who's that?!

284
00:16:38.230 --> 00:16:40.270
He runs so fast!

285
00:16:40.270 --> 00:16:41.560
Is he a samurai?!

286
00:16:41.560 --> 00:16:43.110
A samurai?!

287
00:16:43.610 --> 00:16:44.980
The one I've heard about?!

288
00:16:47.110 --> 00:16:49.150
Quit lagging behind!

289
00:16:49.150 --> 00:16:51.410
Commander Oden! Wait!

290
00:16:51.410 --> 00:16:53.490
Shall I plunder their treasure?!

291
00:16:53.490 --> 00:16:56.080
This is a totally different situation!

292
00:16:56.080 --> 00:16:58.290
Don't mess with the Roger Pirates!

293
00:16:59.040 --> 00:17:01.080
He's not listening at all!

294
00:17:19.810 --> 00:17:22.600
Gun Modoki!

295
00:17:34.490 --> 00:17:36.620
He's as strong as they say.

296
00:17:36.620 --> 00:17:38.910
Should we stop him already, Rayleigh?

297
00:17:38.910 --> 00:17:40.000
Sounds like a plan!

298
00:17:40.000 --> 00:17:42.790
Wait, Gaban! Rayleigh!

299
00:17:42.790 --> 00:17:45.540
I can't have you two getting hurt!

300
00:17:47.590 --> 00:17:49.170
You just wanna fight him.

301
00:17:52.630 --> 00:17:54.550
I smell a beast!

302
00:17:55.680 --> 00:17:57.430
Hey, samurai!

303
00:18:00.060 --> 00:18:01.940
Divine Departure!

304
00:18:24.420 --> 00:18:27.170
What the hell was that?!

305
00:18:30.340 --> 00:18:33.090
Damn! I cannot let that one slide!

306
00:18:44.310 --> 00:18:45.520
There you are!

307
00:18:59.530 --> 00:19:01.120
They are not even touching!

308
00:19:16.900 --> 00:19:18.050
The ship!

309
00:19:26.400 --> 00:19:28.770
You look well...

310
00:19:28.770 --> 00:19:30.480
Roger!

311
00:19:30.480 --> 00:19:32.900
How long has it been...

312
00:19:33.400 --> 00:19:36.070
Newgate?!

313
00:19:51.380 --> 00:19:53.510
– Drop your treasure and beat it!
– Drop your treasure and beat it!

314
00:19:53.510 --> 00:19:54.840
Give 'em hell!

315
00:19:56.010 --> 00:19:57.260
Rob 'em blind!

316
00:19:58.550 --> 00:20:01.470
The two great pirates of the age clashed!

317
00:20:07.940 --> 00:20:11.400
The Roger Pirates versus
the Whitebeard Pirates.

318
00:20:11.400 --> 00:20:12.860
<b>Second Day</b>

319
00:20:11.400 --> 00:20:14.400
This fierce battle lasted
three days and three nights.

320
00:20:18.070 --> 00:20:19.950
Don't underestimate me!

321
00:20:22.410 --> 00:20:25.330
I never underestimate my opponents,

322
00:20:25.330 --> 00:20:26.290
young man.

323
00:20:36.720 --> 00:20:38.720
<b>Third Day</b>

324
00:20:54.520 --> 00:21:04.450
<b>Fourth Day...</b>

325
00:20:54.520 --> 00:20:57.070
Then, three boxes of dried meat for a barrel?!

326
00:20:57.070 --> 00:20:58.200
Deal!

327
00:20:58.200 --> 00:21:00.990
I like this shirt! Where did you get it?!

328
00:21:00.990 --> 00:21:02.660
Let me have more!

329
00:21:02.660 --> 00:21:04.450
Wait! You took too much!

330
00:21:04.450 --> 00:21:07.040
It's all gotta even out!

331
00:21:07.660 --> 00:21:09.160
My bad.

332
00:21:09.160 --> 00:21:11.420
Maybe you can sweeten the deal?

333
00:21:11.420 --> 00:21:12.330
Yeah!

334
00:21:13.080 --> 00:21:16.510
From plundering to exchanging presents...

335
00:21:20.550 --> 00:21:22.800
Are they apprentices?

336
00:21:23.000 --> 00:21:24.930
Huh? Yeah.

337
00:21:24.930 --> 00:21:27.770
Now that you mention it,
they've been here the whole time.

338
00:21:28.230 --> 00:21:30.640
They don't look too tough...

339
00:21:31.690 --> 00:21:33.100
But they behave...

340
00:21:33.520 --> 00:21:35.610
like veterans.

341
00:21:36.360 --> 00:21:37.610
Hey!

342
00:21:37.610 --> 00:21:38.570
Shanks!

343
00:21:38.990 --> 00:21:40.030
What?

344
00:21:40.030 --> 00:21:44.410
You see the guy with the hat over there?

345
00:21:44.410 --> 00:21:45.200
Yeah.

346
00:21:45.580 --> 00:21:50.580
I heard he didn't sleep a wink
during the nightly ceasefires!

347
00:21:51.670 --> 00:21:52.540
Why not?

348
00:21:53.080 --> 00:21:54.080
Is he showing off?

349
00:21:54.080 --> 00:21:55.340
Not even close!

350
00:21:55.340 --> 00:21:59.460
They say, since the day he was born,
he's never slept! Not even once!

351
00:21:59.460 --> 00:22:02.220
Huh? Can such a person exist?

352
00:22:02.220 --> 00:22:04.090
Lucky guy.

353
00:22:04.090 --> 00:22:06.220
I wonder if his life is twice as fun!

354
00:22:06.220 --> 00:22:07.600
Idiot!

355
00:22:07.600 --> 00:22:09.720
It's not that simple!

356
00:22:09.720 --> 00:22:11.730
He must be a monster!

357
00:22:11.730 --> 00:22:13.310
A monster...?

358
00:22:15.440 --> 00:22:17.440
Hey, Oden!

359
00:22:17.440 --> 00:22:19.360
Can you really read it?!

360
00:22:19.730 --> 00:22:21.320
Indeed, I can.

361
00:22:21.320 --> 00:22:25.200
But why in the world
do you possess such writing?!

362
00:22:25.200 --> 00:22:31.250
Wano's Kozuki Clan has passed down knowledge
of this script to only one son per generation.

363
00:22:33.460 --> 00:22:35.790
It's already been thirteen years...

364
00:22:38.170 --> 00:22:43.170
We finally made it to Lodestar Island,
the last island that the log pose points to,

365
00:22:42.340 --> 00:22:46.590
<b>Lodestar Island</b>

366
00:22:43.170 --> 00:22:46.600
which no man has ever set foot upon.

367
00:22:47.220 --> 00:22:50.430
But our celebration
was cut short, as we realized...

368
00:22:51.060 --> 00:22:53.980
that it wasn't the final island!

369
00:22:54.690 --> 00:22:59.860
The needles on the log pose just kept
spinning and wouldn't lock on to anything!

370
00:22:59.860 --> 00:23:02.240
I was convinced.

371
00:23:02.240 --> 00:23:04.820
There had to be one more island!

372
00:23:04.820 --> 00:23:11.700
When I make it there, I'll be the first person
ever to travel all around the world!

373
00:23:12.330 --> 00:23:19.040
And the location of said island is hidden
in the script of these four red stones!

374
00:23:19.880 --> 00:23:26.130
But the World Government has always
forbidden anyone from deciphering them.

375
00:23:26.550 --> 00:23:29.220
They're called poneglyphs.

376
00:23:30.010 --> 00:23:34.640
<b>Lodestar Island</b>

377
00:23:30.010 --> 00:23:33.100
I thought they were just cultural artifacts,

378
00:23:33.100 --> 00:23:38.980
but they're actually the vital map
that'll point us to the final island's location.

379
00:23:34.640 --> 00:23:36.890
<b>Lodestar Island</b>

380
00:23:41.400 --> 00:23:45.200
The government is telling us
not to go to the final island,

381
00:23:45.200 --> 00:23:47.530
which is said to contain treasure untold!

382
00:23:48.030 --> 00:23:50.660
That makes it all the more tantalizing!

383
00:23:50.990 --> 00:23:54.870
If we can reach it, we will be,
in both name and in deed...

384
00:23:54.870 --> 00:23:58.040
the world's greatest pirate crew!

385
00:24:03.630 --> 00:24:05.220
The world's greatest?

386
00:24:05.720 --> 00:24:07.300
That's right!

387
00:24:07.300 --> 00:24:10.100
And then, I'll...!

388
00:24:29.570 --> 00:24:31.910
I could not move.

389
00:24:31.910 --> 00:24:35.040
For the second time that day,
I was left speechless.

390
00:24:35.160 --> 00:24:37.120
Who exactly is this man?!

391
00:24:46.630 --> 00:24:49.010
What are you talking about, Roger?!

392
00:24:49.010 --> 00:24:50.970
That's a child's fantasy!

393
00:24:57.640 --> 00:25:00.350
I'm serious, Newgate!

394
00:25:01.060 --> 00:25:02.150
Please!

395
00:25:03.650 --> 00:25:05.400
I only need him for a year.

396
00:25:05.400 --> 00:25:07.740
Let me borrow Oden!

397
00:25:07.740 --> 00:25:09.860
This is my last request!

398
00:25:09.860 --> 00:25:13.700
With him, I'm sure I can get to the final island!

399
00:25:15.200 --> 00:25:18.080
Hey, maybe you should ask me first!

400
00:25:19.080 --> 00:25:21.710
Please, Newgate!

401
00:25:23.330 --> 00:25:24.920
I'm begging you!

402
00:25:24.920 --> 00:25:28.920
Hey, stop, Captain Roger! He's our enemy!

403
00:25:31.590 --> 00:25:33.850
Stop! That is beneath you!

404
00:25:33.850 --> 00:25:35.930
Do not bow your head!

405
00:25:36.350 --> 00:25:38.480
Please, Oden!

406
00:25:38.480 --> 00:25:42.350
Accompany us on our journey for just a year!

407
00:25:43.980 --> 00:25:45.940
Screw you!

408
00:25:48.900 --> 00:25:52.780
Roger! Are you trying to take
my family away from me?!

409
00:25:53.320 --> 00:25:56.240
But I could not help feeling excited!

410
00:25:57.200 --> 00:26:00.460
Why can the Kozuki Clan read the script?

411
00:26:01.540 --> 00:26:04.580
Why have our paths crossed?

412
00:26:12.300 --> 00:26:16.180
Before I knew it, the words
burst forth from my mouth!

413
00:26:17.510 --> 00:26:19.220
Whitekichi!

414
00:26:19.220 --> 00:26:20.850
I want to go with him!

415
00:26:21.270 --> 00:26:23.730
Please allow me to go!

416
00:26:23.730 --> 00:26:27.730
I wish to see this final island
he speaks of with my own eyes!

417
00:26:31.690 --> 00:26:33.360
You look annoyed!

418
00:26:33.360 --> 00:26:35.700
Of course I do!

419
00:26:36.030 --> 00:26:38.790
You're like a brother to me!

420
00:26:38.790 --> 00:26:41.040
It will only be a year, Whitekichi!

421
00:26:49.840 --> 00:26:51.210
Please!

422
00:26:56.010 --> 00:26:57.510
Take care of yourself!

423
00:26:57.510 --> 00:26:58.970
I will!

424
00:26:59.390 --> 00:27:01.390
We have decided to remain behind.

425
00:27:02.390 --> 00:27:04.140
We are fond of this ship.

426
00:27:04.140 --> 00:27:07.020
We await your return here.

427
00:27:12.650 --> 00:27:14.280
Sure thing.

428
00:27:14.280 --> 00:27:16.700
Men, you are fully-fledged pirates now!

429
00:27:17.950 --> 00:27:19.620
Let us all do as we please!

430
00:27:25.620 --> 00:27:28.960
Pops! Aren't you gonna send him off?

431
00:27:32.010 --> 00:27:35.220
Roger left us quite the thank-you gift.

432
00:27:35.220 --> 00:27:37.140
Tons of treasure!

433
00:27:37.140 --> 00:27:39.260
And look at all the grub!

434
00:27:39.720 --> 00:27:40.970
What?!

435
00:27:40.970 --> 00:27:43.310
You morons!

436
00:27:43.310 --> 00:27:46.060
Give the food back to them!

437
00:27:46.060 --> 00:27:51.440
I won't forgive them if they let
Kozuki Oden's family go hungry!

438
00:27:51.440 --> 00:27:53.070
Hurry up!

439
00:27:53.070 --> 00:27:54.280
Yes!

440
00:27:54.280 --> 00:27:55.860
Right away!

441
00:28:00.370 --> 00:28:02.540
Lord Oden!

442
00:28:06.080 --> 00:28:11.210
I will see you again, everyone!

443
00:28:11.920 --> 00:28:14.380
Give it your all!

444
00:28:15.010 --> 00:28:19.590
Can't wait to hear the story of your journey!

445
00:28:19.590 --> 00:28:21.970
Take care of yourselves!

446
00:28:32.730 --> 00:28:35.860
The second chapter of my
life as a pirate was starting.

447
00:28:36.360 --> 00:28:38.700
A new adventure was on the horizon!

448
00:28:39.200 --> 00:28:44.660
While Whitekichi is a great man,
Roger has an incalculable depth to him.

449
00:28:45.250 --> 00:28:47.500
Fortune has truly smiled upon me!

450
00:28:51.330 --> 00:28:54.550
Oh, good girl, good girl.

451
00:28:54.550 --> 00:28:56.630
Up, up!

452
00:28:57.760 --> 00:29:00.550
It's been so long since we last held a baby!

453
00:29:00.550 --> 00:29:01.800
Yeah.

454
00:29:01.800 --> 00:29:03.720
It brings back memories.

455
00:29:04.260 --> 00:29:07.390
Momonosuke and Hiyori...

456
00:29:11.310 --> 00:29:12.400
Okay?

457
00:29:12.400 --> 00:29:14.190
Here we go! Boo!

458
00:29:20.150 --> 00:29:21.910
Captain Roger!

459
00:29:21.910 --> 00:29:23.280
We have stowaways!

460
00:29:26.290 --> 00:29:29.000
– Lord Oden!
– Lord Oden!

461
00:29:29.410 --> 00:29:30.670
Inuarashi!

462
00:29:30.670 --> 00:29:32.540
Nekomamushi!

463
00:29:34.460 --> 00:29:36.250
What are you doing here?!

464
00:29:36.250 --> 00:29:40.970
We enjoy your company meow than anyone's!

465
00:29:41.590 --> 00:29:43.970
The dog and the cat have vanished!

466
00:29:44.390 --> 00:29:47.770
Those morons...!

467
00:29:51.270 --> 00:29:55.860
Oden! You're only here because
the captain needs your expertise.

468
00:29:55.860 --> 00:29:57.320
Understood?

469
00:29:59.900 --> 00:30:02.610
<b>Mock Town, Jaya</b>

470
00:30:02.610 --> 00:30:05.160
Next, radishes!

471
00:30:05.160 --> 00:30:06.580
Thief!

472
00:30:06.580 --> 00:30:08.700
Captain's gonna kill him.

473
00:30:11.500 --> 00:30:14.420
Oden! Leave the civilians alone!

474
00:30:14.420 --> 00:30:16.790
I still need many more ingredients!

475
00:30:16.790 --> 00:30:18.050
Ingredients for what?!

476
00:30:24.430 --> 00:30:27.390
You've got some nerve!

477
00:30:29.850 --> 00:30:33.310
Huh?! Is this town actually lawless?!

478
00:30:33.310 --> 00:30:34.850
Gaban, they're...

479
00:30:34.850 --> 00:30:36.360
Yeah.

480
00:30:36.360 --> 00:30:38.400
Guess they're not civilians after all.

481
00:30:52.290 --> 00:30:53.250
Oden!

482
00:30:53.250 --> 00:30:54.870
He took it full-on!

483
00:30:56.880 --> 00:30:58.460
Oden!

484
00:31:13.100 --> 00:31:14.940
Oden! You...

485
00:31:15.770 --> 00:31:16.980
He's alive!

486
00:31:16.980 --> 00:31:18.150
Wow!

487
00:31:20.150 --> 00:31:23.530
Gaban, they're not civilians, right?

488
00:31:24.570 --> 00:31:26.030
No, they're not...

489
00:31:27.870 --> 00:31:28.910
Oden.

490
00:31:29.740 --> 00:31:30.490
Okay.

491
00:31:34.120 --> 00:31:36.120
I still need some kelp!

492
00:31:36.120 --> 00:31:37.630
Kelp?!

493
00:31:37.630 --> 00:31:39.420
It makes for a fine broth.

494
00:31:44.800 --> 00:31:46.050
You're so strange!

495
00:31:47.180 --> 00:31:49.760
Ah, screw it!

496
00:31:50.180 --> 00:31:51.680
Get 'em!

497
00:31:55.940 --> 00:32:03.900
– Oden!
– Oden!

498
00:32:03.900 --> 00:32:06.740
♪ Oh, radish, ganmo! ♪

499
00:32:08.200 --> 00:32:10.620
♪ Chikuwa and eggs! ♪

500
00:32:12.080 --> 00:32:16.040
♪ One, two, three, go ahead and eat! ♪

501
00:32:16.040 --> 00:32:18.500
♪ Oden was meant... ♪

502
00:32:20.250 --> 00:32:23.460
♪ to boil! ♪

503
00:32:31.050 --> 00:32:32.850
Huh? Captain, did you catch a cold?

504
00:32:33.430 --> 00:32:36.020
Yeah, but it's nothing.

505
00:32:36.020 --> 00:32:38.310
It is something, you fool!

506
00:32:38.310 --> 00:32:40.980
He's only got a year to live at most!

507
00:32:40.980 --> 00:32:42.480
What?!

508
00:32:44.190 --> 00:32:47.320
I'm living life at top speed.

509
00:32:51.370 --> 00:32:54.370
It's coming... The Knock-Up Stream!

510
00:33:05.210 --> 00:33:06.590
I'm gonna die!

511
00:33:22.860 --> 00:33:23.980
An island!

512
00:33:27.150 --> 00:33:28.490
So that's...

513
00:33:33.820 --> 00:33:35.410
The sky island!

514
00:33:35.410 --> 00:33:38.450
Welcome, Blue Sea denizens.
You've traveled quite a ways.

515
00:33:39.540 --> 00:33:41.420
– Heso!
– Heso!

516
00:33:43.790 --> 00:33:46.750
The world is so vast!
There is no end to its wonders!

517
00:33:46.750 --> 00:33:51.340
Buddha himself could not have imagined
that people were living in the sky!

518
00:34:00.390 --> 00:34:03.770
It takes at least ten years to handle a waver.

519
00:34:12.490 --> 00:34:14.740
Run!

520
00:34:26.250 --> 00:34:29.170
So this is the City of Gold, Shandora!

521
00:34:29.170 --> 00:34:30.630
– Wow!
– Wow!

522
00:34:31.380 --> 00:34:33.470
I found it!

523
00:34:33.470 --> 00:34:35.090
It was all the way up here?!

524
00:34:41.480 --> 00:34:44.400
That must be the grand bell of Shandora!

525
00:34:44.400 --> 00:34:46.230
It's pure gold!

526
00:34:46.230 --> 00:34:48.570
Captain, how will we bring it back with us?

527
00:34:48.570 --> 00:34:50.530
I don't have time.

528
00:34:50.530 --> 00:34:54.530
Once you become a captain,
come get it yourself, Buggy.

529
00:34:54.530 --> 00:34:56.120
What?!

530
00:34:56.120 --> 00:34:58.240
We can at least grab a piece now!

531
00:34:58.240 --> 00:35:02.580
With such a strong voice,
this stone was easy to locate.

532
00:35:02.580 --> 00:35:04.920
It's talking about a great power, right?

533
00:35:14.340 --> 00:35:17.720
The text speaks of a weapon
by the name of Poseidon.

534
00:35:17.720 --> 00:35:18.720
I see...

535
00:35:20.390 --> 00:35:23.980
Oden, you can also write the script, right?!

536
00:35:23.980 --> 00:35:25.900
Yes, of course.

537
00:35:26.650 --> 00:35:28.020
Then carve this message!

538
00:35:37.070 --> 00:35:39.620
Roger is near the end of his life...

539
00:35:39.620 --> 00:35:43.500
It is difficult the fathom,
but if he is living with such urgency,

540
00:35:43.500 --> 00:35:45.830
I will follow him to the end!

541
00:35:48.000 --> 00:35:49.290
How is it?

542
00:35:50.590 --> 00:35:52.800
It's perfect, Oden!

543
00:35:53.630 --> 00:35:55.630
"I made it here.

544
00:35:55.630 --> 00:35:58.510
I will guide this text to the ends of the world.

545
00:35:58.510 --> 00:36:00.970
Pirate Gol D. Roger."

546
00:36:11.690 --> 00:36:14.150
I must see it, Roger.

547
00:36:14.150 --> 00:36:18.360
The final chapter of the great adventure
to which you have devoted your life!

548
00:36:26.580 --> 00:36:29.670
Men! Let's go back to the Blue Sea!

549
00:36:29.670 --> 00:36:31.460
– Yeah!
– Yeah!
